model.interfaces.dataStores.future.impute

Interface ImputeMissingOccurrences


  • public interface ImputeMissingOccurrences
    ----- Calculation and imputation methods ----- NOTE: There is a difference between calculation and imputation. Calculating data means we are filling in fields based on information we hold in other fields but the same year e.g. calculating the male to female ratio for 1992 using the data we hold about the size of the male and female populations in 1992 Imputing data means we are filling in fields based on information we hold in the same field but for different years e.g. imputing that the size of the male population is 1000 in 1992 based on the information that the male population in 1991 and 1993 was 950 and 1050 respectively.
